description: From amber (“yellow color”) + jack (“fish of family Carangidae”).

entries.meaning: Any of several large food and game yellowtail fishes of the genus Seriola, found in warm waters of all oceans.
examples: It was an amberjack, and twice as large as any I had ever seen before. As I drew up the captain's snapper this amberjack came to the surface, and I certainly yelled.
